(134, 1, '2020-10-12 08:30:04', '2020-10-12 08:30:04', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Financial institutions, like many companies in other sectors, had to quickly adapt to supporting the needs of their employees and customers in what became an almost exclusively digital world when the COVID-19 pandemic first hit the United States in March.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For TD Bank, one of the nation’s 10 largest banks, a deep understanding of customers, as well as empathy and transparency for employees, has been a winning formula for success during this time of unprecedented uncertainty.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this exclusive interview with Tyrrell Schmidt, CMO of TD Bank and head of global brand for TD Bank Group, we learn about what the pandemic has taught her about leadership, business, hiring, and managing employees.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3 id="what-makes-td-different-than-other-banks">What makes TD different than other banks?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s the people. We truly have a culture that values its colleagues. It’s built on a foundation and culture of caring, which I think is unique and makes people want to come to work at TD and want to stay with us.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The other thing that sets us apart is our deep belief in customer-centricity. We put the customer at the center of all of our decisions, including how we think about bringing our brand to our communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For example, in the U.S., one of the key pillars or tenets of our brand is knowing and being part of our local communities. So, whether that’s knowing the small businesses that are there or having a strong local field marketing team who brings our brand to life in our communities, it’s a core differentiator.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'TD Bank CMO: Communication, empathy, and transparency key to leadership during crisis', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'td-bank-cmo-communication-empathy-and-transparency-key-to-leadership-during-crisis__trashed', '', '', '2020-10-12 08:47:02', '2020-10-12 08:47:02', '', 0, 'http://server.visionvivante.com:8080/review_system/blog/?p=134', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(135, 1, '2020-10-12 08:30:02', '2020-10-12 08:30:02', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When Bill VanCuren joined NCR in 1984 the then-century-old, Dayton, Ohio-based computer manufacturing company was focused on maintaining its position and brand image as the “cash register” company.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some 36 years later, everything has changed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Not only was our approach to IT and marketing radically different at the time, NCR was positioned and thought of as an almost entirely different company,” says VanCuren, who serves as NCR’s senior vice president and CIO.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Over the past six years, VanCuren has worked hand in hand with Marija Zivanovic-Smith, the company’s senior vice president of corporate marketing, communications, and chief external affairs officer, to transform NCR’s customer engagement strategy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Not only have our strategies and tactics changed, but the narratives and technology driving them have as well,” adds Zivanovic-Smith, who joined NCR in 2008.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The two executives have been focused, specifically, on retooling NCR’s marketing and IT infrastructure to compete in the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.adobe.com/marketing/experience-manager/benefits.html" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">digital experience</a>&nbsp;economy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“This coincides with our evolution as a company into the software- and services-led enterprise provider we are today,” VanCuren says. “This required us to dig deep internally and understand the gaps and synergies between IT and marketing to create a vision for NCR’s digital strategy.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here’s a closer look at how they’ve collaborated over the years, from the early days of&nbsp;<a href="https://magento.com/solutions/digital-transformation" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">digital transformation</a>&nbsp;to managing the many challenges brought on by the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'NCR: From ‘cash register’ company to digital leader', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ncr-from-cash-register-company-to-digital-leader', '', '', '2020-10-12 08:30:03', '2020-10-12 08:30:03', '', 0, 'http://server.visionvivante.com:8080/review_system/blog/?p=135', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(136, 1, '2020-10-12 08:29:59', '2020-10-12 08:29:59', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The evolving realities of a digitally driven society were punctuated with the acceleration of e-commerce during the COVID-19 disruption for businesses.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Over the past months we have seen brands turning hundreds of stores into instant pick, pack, and ship locations to keep up with staggering demands, as well as businesses adding direct-to-consumer (DTC) capabilities overnight via&nbsp;<a href="https://magento.com/products/magento-commerce" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">Magento Commerce</a>&nbsp;to move stagnant inventory.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>E-commerce leaders, partnered with their IT, operations, and marketing counterparts, need more than just a one-size-fits-all&nbsp;<a href="https://www.adobe.com/marketing/experience-manager-sites/ecommerce-integrations.html" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">e-commerce solution</a>. They require an agile&nbsp;<a href="https://magento.com/products/magento-commerce" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">e-commerce platform</a>&nbsp;that is flexible when external or internal conditions necessitate change. All the while, companies can’t afford for these pivots to take months or years to materialize.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Adobe is transforming the way brands and businesses think about e-commerce. An example of this is Carrier Enterprise, which created an agile yet easy-to-use buying experience for its contractor customers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“We have embraced the agility offered by the Magento platform as we weave technology into every touchpoint and respond to customer feedback through quick iterations, while rapidly improving the overall experience,” says Ed Gaffney, president of e-commerce at Carrier Enterprise. “Magento, at the core of our B2B transformation, has increased sales and further strengthened our relationship with our customers.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We believe Adobe’s latest recognition as a Leader in the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.adobe.com/offer/Gartner-Magic-Quadrant-for-Digital-Commerce-2020.html" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">Gartner Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce</a>, for the fourth year in a row, reinforces the commerce vision and roadmap we’ve been executing. Adobe has been evaluated as a Leader since our acquisition of Magento in June 2018. We were one of 15 vendors that were evaluated in the report for their ability to execute and completeness of vision.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Adobe named a leader in the 2020 Gartner Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'adobe-named-a-leader-in-the-2020-gartner-magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce', '', '', '2020-10-12 08:30:00', '2020-10-12 08:30:00', '', 0, 'http://server.visionvivante.com:8080/review_system/blog/?p=136', 0, 'post', '', 0),
